<p class="p">For the pre-1963 layers, the dates were calculated as below:
 <disp-formula id="FD4-ijerph-15-02734" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(4)</label>
  <math id="mm4" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
      <mo class="mo">=</mo>
      <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
      <mn class="mn">1963</mn>
      <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
      <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mi class="mi">ln</mi>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">A</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">w</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">A</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where, A
 <sub class="sub">i</sub> is the cumulative inventory of excess 
 <sup class="sup">210</sup>Pb below layer i (Bq kg
 <sup class="sup">−1</sup>).
